story_txt:
The Public Record is Hamilton's local news funded by Hamiltonians, written by Hamiltonians for all Hamiltonians. Founded and produced by Hamilton independent journalist Joey Coleman, The Public Record covers Hamilton's civic affairs in-depth thanks to its reader funding model. At a time when many communities are suffering from news deficits, Hamilton City Hall is covered by The Public Record including sub-committees, committees and Council. Reader Funding Makes Possible
Investigative journalism, including freedom of information fees, to uncover issues such as the HSR transit crisis, city spending, planning, and community concerns;
In-depth journalism on municipal affairs including our recent in-depth coverage of the Ontario Municipal Board hearing on Hamilton's ward boundaries;
Equipment purchases and maintenance to film, audio record, and photograph meetings, civic events, and produce The Public Record Radio Show;

Business planning expenses for expansion of The Public Record in 2018, including planning to hire freelance contributors to ensure every ward race is covered, and every public debate is recorded;
Overhead expenses including office, server hosting, equipment maintenance, cellular expenses, and all the associated expenses in creating high-quality original journalism;
Continuing coverage of Hamilton's civic affairs; and more.
Contributing to The Public Record's crowdfunding campaign is the best value in local journalism, anywhere.A New Model of Local Journalism for EveryoneTo be effective in providing a public goal, public interest journalism must be accessible to all. To be sustainable, it must be funded by readers.This crowdfunding campaign will enable The Public Record to implement its 90-9-1 model of reader financial support to make local journalism sustainable.The monthly patron model is the only one that can sustain watchdog journalism.It enables an outlet to assign journalists with a long-term commitment to fearless journalism, to launch investigations into problems needing solutions, and to be free from undue influence.Investing in this crowdfunding campaign will enable me to get to sustainability and grow. My next goal is simple, I want to be able to hire Hamiltonians to cover Hamilton as we grow The Public Record.The Benefits to AllYour support enables everyone to:
Benefit from a more informed community conversation;
Accurate, Responsible real-time reporting; and
Access to public information.
Every City Council meeting, every City Council committee, every City Council sub-committee, School Board meetings, Public meetings, Local Events, Art Crawls, Town Halls, and more - that's the journalism your contribution supports.The Public Record's Policies and AffiliationsAs a professional news agency, The Public Record strives to reach and uphold the highest standards of journalism. The Public Record is a member of the National Newsmedia Council, Canada's self-regulatory body for professional news outlets. Joey Coleman is a member of the Canadian Association of Journalists.The Public Record's policies can be read on our website:
Our Mission
Our Code of Ethics and Journalistic Practice
